{"lemma":"فَجَرَةٍ","slug":"فَجَرَةٍ","root":"ف.ج.ر","root_slug":"ف-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ج-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فاجِر","root":"فجر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33043","n33051","n33052","n33053"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of فَجَرَ (fajara)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of فَجَرَ (fajara); wicked, sinful, ungodly","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ الْأَبْرَارَ لَفِي نَعِيمٍ / وَإِنَّ الْفُجَّارَ لَفِي جَحِيمٍ","english":"Indeed the pious will be in bliss, and lo, the wicked will be in the fire of hell."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/faː.d͡ʒir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33043","headword_ar":"فجّرهُ","root":"fjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, near the beginning.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fujuwr","text_ar":"فُجُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vice, immorality, unrighteousness, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1)]; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fas~aqahu","text_ar":"فَسَّقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence the phrase, in a trad. of Ibn-Ez-Zubeyr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faj~arota binafosika","text_ar":"فَجَّرْتَ بِنَفْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast attributed to thyself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused thyself of, unrighteousness, transgression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33051","headword_ar":"فَجْرَةُ","root":"fjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is a proper name, [i. e. an attributive proper name,] imperfectly decl., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bar~apu","text_ar":"بَرَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [and signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfajorapu","text_ar":"الفَجْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAri","text_ar":"فَجَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAri","text_ar":"فَجَارِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is altered from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajorapN","text_ar":"فَجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IJ, TA,) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfajorapu","text_ar":"الفَجْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, TA,) and is a subst. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfujuwru","text_ar":"الفُجُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vice, immorality, wickedness, unrighteousness, sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transgression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (see 1,)] (S,) or a name for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfajorapu","text_ar":"الفَجْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same], (O,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAmi","text_ar":"قَطَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) determinate, (S,) occurring in a verse of En-Nábighah cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hml","text_ar":"حمل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba fulaAnN fajorapa","text_ar":"رَكِبَ فُلَانٌ فَجْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajarapa","text_ar":"فَجَرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAri","text_ar":"فَجَارِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one lied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted vitiously"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajara","text_ar":"فَجَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halafa","text_ar":"حَلَفَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN EalaY fajorapa","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عَلَى فَجْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otamala EalaY fajorapa","text_ar":"اِشْتَمَلَ عَلَى فَجْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the L"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY fajorihi","text_ar":"على فَجْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in both instances, but the former is the right reading,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one commited a foul deed, by swearing falsely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[relating to the former phrase,] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by adultery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IJ","TA","Sb","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n33052","headword_ar":"فُجْرَةٌ","root":"fjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafojarN","text_ar":"مَفْجَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33053","headword_ar":"فِجْرَةٌ","root":"fjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last of a woman's children;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinoyapN","text_ar":"زِنْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the “ last of a man's children. ” (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"znY","text_ar":"زنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}